storyInfo: Cuora is out to buy gifts for her friends, but ends up entangled in a 'battle' over her backpack.

attributes.content: Hm... according to the map, this should be the street market.
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Wow, there's so many stalls, way more than I imagined... Uh oh, I'm starting to worry maybe I didn't bring enough money.
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Wow, crystal dumplings! And lotus seed buns! So much tasty food... I'll buy some just to try, they can't cost that much, right?
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Om nom... Burp! I'm so full!
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Oh no! I can't eat anymore! I came to buy gifts for everybody!
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Sigh, this is all my fault. I got mad at Cardi when she stepped on my backpack...
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: I didn't mean to, but my backpack...
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: I finally made friends with everybody, I can't let it stay like this!
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: I'll pick a good present, and then apologize to Cardi!
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: The luster, the pattern, the weight...
attributes.name: Shrewd Youth

attributes.content: No mistaking it, we're gonna be rich this time!
attributes.name: Shrewd Youth

attributes.content: Hmph. That Columbian lady just looked at us funny.
attributes.name: Shrewd Youth

attributes.content: Don't be so haughty! If you don't look after your stuff, somebody else will look after it for you!
attributes.name: Shrewd Youth

attributes.content: Damn, daai goh. Barely three words and you scammed that right up...
attributes.name: Careless Youth

attributes.content: That bitch has no clue what just happened to her!
attributes.name: Careless Youth

attributes.content: That wasn't no scam, dumbass, I asked permission.
attributes.name: Shrewd Youth

attributes.content: We do what we've gotta do to feed ourselves. Is it so wrong to ask Heaven for permission to snatch something?
attributes.name: Shrewd Youth

attributes.content: Wow, you're right! But...
attributes.name: Careless Youth

attributes.content: What is it, kiddo? Out with it!
attributes.name: Shrewd Youth

attributes.content: I kinda wanna touch that pendant...
attributes.name: Careless Youth

attributes.content: Here! Over by the window, in the sunlight, the patterns really stand out!
attributes.name: Shrewd Youth

attributes.content: Wowza, this foreign stuff is way different from what we get in Lungmen.
attributes.name: Careless Youth

attributes.content: Hm? This part... is it supposed to be some kind of beast? There's something on its back—
attributes.name: Careless Youth

attributes.content: The young man's hand slips and the pendant drops out the window.
Excuse me! I want one of these and one of those!
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Alright, alright, girl, let me wrap them up for you.
attributes.name: Street Stall Owner

attributes.content: I don't need a bag, I can put them right into my backpack!
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Oh, I need to pay though... Um, my wallet should be in my jacket pocket.
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: The pendant falls into Cuora's open backpack without anyone noticing.
You don't look like a Lungmenite. Are you here on vacation? Let me give you a discount! Here's your change.
attributes.name: Street Stall Owner

attributes.content: You're buying a lot. Is it for your parents?
attributes.name: Street Stall Owner

attributes.content: No, for my friends!
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: The girl here has a lot of friends, huh? Here, take some freebies.
attributes.name: Street Stall Owner

attributes.content: It's all the best Lungmen has to offer, handmade. Share with your friends!
attributes.name: Street Stall Owner

attributes.content: Thank you, mister!
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Don't mention it! I hope you have fun in Lungmen. And uh, keep an eye on your things...
attributes.name: Street Stall Owner

attributes.content: There've been a lot of pickpockets around here lately. They especially like targeting foreigners.
attributes.name: Street Stall Owner

attributes.content: Got it! Now I know I may not look it, but I'm really good at fighting!
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: If I see a pickpocket, I'll send him flying!
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: I never knew the Lungmenites were so friendly! That guy gave me a ton of stuff...
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: I'll pick through it all when I get back and hand stuff out to everyone at Rhodes Island!
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Those little animal figures would be perfect for Adnachiel and Steward...
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: And that Yanese silk cap would be great for May!
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: The music box would be good for Lava, and the scarf for Instructor Dobermann...
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Sigh, but after going all over the place, I still don't have anything for Cardi.
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: What can I give her?
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Wait a second there, girl!
attributes.name: Careless Youth

attributes.content: Huh? What's wrong?
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: I dropped something out the window and it landed in that souvenir stall over there. A metal pendant, did you happen to see it?
attributes.name: Careless Youth

attributes.content: Hm? No, I didn't.
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: I did. It fell right into your backpack. Would you mind opening it for me so I can take a look?
attributes.name: Careless Youth

attributes.content: Just a sec, I'll check...
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: All the little souvenirs that guy gave me are metal thingies... You didn't come over to bother me just because you saw all that, did you?
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: How dare you!
attributes.name: Careless Youth

attributes.content: Gimme that bag, I'll find it!
attributes.name: Careless Youth

attributes.content: Hand's off! Don't touch my backpack!
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Hmph! You're trying to steal from me? You'll have to ask my baseball bat first!
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Half an hour later...
Hmm, yeah.
attributes.name: Careless Youth

attributes.content: Good idea, ah goh, I'll start putting it together!
attributes.name: Careless Youth

attributes.content: Don't mess it up this time!
attributes.name: Shrewd Youth

attributes.content: Dammit, that little dumbass is short on success and long on failure.
attributes.name: Shrewd Youth

attributes.content: I can't believe a little girl like that put him on the ground in just a couple of moves.
attributes.name: Shrewd Youth

attributes.content: If you can't use your fists, you gotta use your brain. Let's change it up.
attributes.name: Shrewd Youth

attributes.content: It's just like the souvenir shop guy said... do I look like such a clueless tourist?
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: I guess Lungmen's got a real problem with crime and safety...
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: You there, girl, hold up a second!
attributes.name: Shrewd Youth

attributes.content: Who are you?
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Hey, don't get the wrong idea. I just heard you talking about how Lungmen isn't safe, so I figured I'd ask what's up.
attributes.name: Shrewd Youth

attributes.content: Here's my badge, these blocks are my beat here.
attributes.name: Shrewd Youth

attributes.content: Lungmen... Block Manager? What do you do?
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: (I've got all kinds of stuff like this prepped and ready. Another badge, another bit of insurance. Let's try this one on for size.)
attributes.name: Shrewd Youth

attributes.content: I keep order on the streets and help out the residents.
attributes.name: Block Manager?

attributes.content: Did you encounter something that upset you?
attributes.name: Block Manager?

attributes.content: We've gotten some reports around here of street vendors selling counterfeit goods to tourists at jacked up prices. I'm undercover investigating.
attributes.name: Block Manager?

attributes.content: If anything like that happened to you, I might be able to help.
attributes.name: Block Manager?

attributes.content: Well... The vendor guy over there was actually really nice. He gave me a discount and a whole bunch of freebies, actually...
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: I mean, I bought a whole bunch of stuff, and I don't feel like I spent that much. Definitely feels cheaper than back in Columbia...
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Oh, but there was this guy back there who tried to steal my stuff!
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Oh? Could you describe his appearance, what he was wearing maybe?
attributes.name: Block Manager?

attributes.content: Uh... he was a man, taller than me, and well... um, I don't really remember what he looked like...
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: That's not much to go on. I don't think I'd be able to find him with just this.
attributes.name: Block Manager?

attributes.content: Never mind. I need to focus on getting a gift for Cardi anyway. Thanks for the offer, Mr. Block Manager. I'd better get going.
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: You need to buy something for your friend? What kind of thing are you looking for?
attributes.name: Block Manager?

attributes.content: I've been working these blocks for years. Maybe I can point you in the right direction.
attributes.name: Block Manager?

attributes.content: I'm not sure how it is in other countries, but us Lungmen Block Managers, we work hard to help our citizens solve problems!
attributes.name: Block Manager?

attributes.content: After all, as a Lungmen public servant, I can't let a foreigner leave with the impression that this city isn't safe.
attributes.name: Block Manager?

attributes.content: If you've got anything troubling you, ma'am, just let me know.
attributes.name: Block Manager?

attributes.content: Oh, okay...
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Well, you see... I got into sort of a fight with a friend, and I want to get her an apology gift...
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: But I've been all over the place, and I still haven't found the right gift.
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: It's not like I haven't bought anything, it's just nothing I've bought feels right.
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: When you're giving your friend a gift, it's the thought that counts, right?
attributes.name: Block Manager?

attributes.content: I've got a short temper and I blow up on my friends sometimes, but when it comes down to it, we're always cool after sharing a meal, a drink, and an apology.
attributes.name: Block Manager?

attributes.content: So, did you apologize to that friend of yours yet?
attributes.name: Block Manager?

attributes.content: Not yet... I mean, it's really hard to know how and when to start.
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Do you know the kinds of things she likes?
attributes.name: Block Manager?

attributes.content: Umm... what does Cardi like?
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: I think I remember Adnachiel saying that Cardi wants to be a skier.
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: And I saw some ski clothes gathering dust in her room...
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Then you should get her a gift a skier would like, right?
attributes.name: Block Manager?

attributes.content: Um... but I don't know anything about skiing.
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Hah, yeah, I get the impression you're more into baseball.
attributes.name: Block Manager?

attributes.content: Do you play? Or just watch?
attributes.name: Block Manager?

attributes.content: I play! I love baseball!
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Then why not get her a baseball gift? If it's something you like, that makes a good gift too.
attributes.name: Block Manager?

attributes.content: Um... but I don't think Cardi is into baseball.
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: I put together a game on the Rhodes Island deck before, but she didn't show...
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Yeah, speaking of baseball, I just remembered the mall on that block over there has some sort of game where you win prizes playing baseball. Want to check it out?
attributes.name: Block Manager?

attributes.content: If you can't think of what to get her, you can just give her whatever prize you win.
attributes.name: Block Manager?

attributes.content: A gift won by your own effort has more meaning to it than something you bought, right?
attributes.name: Block Manager?

attributes.content: That makes sense. Lava did say that handmade gifts are better, but I don't have much talent for crafts...
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Baseball is what I'm best at, so a prize won in baseball should be good.
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Let's take a look! It's been a while since I played, and it'll be a nice chance to have some fun!
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: The games are over there. Looks like it's pretty quiet, so head on over!
attributes.name: Block Manager?

attributes.content: You mean the place with the funny machine?
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Step right up, swing the bat, hit the ball, and win a prize! Today's the last day, hurry on over!
attributes.name: Arcade Worker?

attributes.content: (Ugh, that idiot's dressed up as an arcade worker. Looks convincing enough.)
attributes.name: Block Manager?

attributes.content: (Making use of this arcade that just closed, getting the girl to take the bait, it's almost too easy... I really am a genius!)
attributes.name: Block Manager?

attributes.content: Hi there! Is this the place where you play baseball? What are your prizes?
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Oh, uh... prizes, yeah...
attributes.name: Arcade Worker?

attributes.content: Wow! All that stuff behind the glass there? That's all the prizes?
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: How about that one! Can I get the snowboard?
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: You want the snowboard? Well, that's the grand prize. Pretty tough to win that one...
attributes.name: Arcade Worker?

attributes.content: Hmm, why do I feel like this guy is kinda familiar...?
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Miss, I gotta warn you, no matter how much you saddle up to me, I'm not gonna make the challenge easier for you.
attributes.name: Arcade Worker?

attributes.content: See that pitching machine? When you hit the ball back, the scoreboard there will rate you based on where the ball hits.
attributes.name: Arcade Worker?

attributes.content: So, if I hit the red center, I get the grand prize?
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: It's not that simple! You pay 40 Lungmen Dollars for a round, you get ten balls per round, and if your score is over 475, you get the grand prize.
attributes.name: Arcade Worker?

attributes.content: Wanna try?
attributes.name: Arcade Worker?

attributes.content: 475 points means hitting the red center five times, isn't that a bit too hard? Are the other prizes easier to get?
attributes.name: Block Manager?

attributes.content: (What are you doing, why are you making it so hard? Nobody would take a challenge that tough. She'll give up after she fails once!)
attributes.name: Block Manager?

attributes.content: Sure, we encourage everyone to try a whole lot.
attributes.name: Arcade Worker?

attributes.content: If you score less than 475, the threshold for the grand prize goes down a bit, to a minimum of 200.
attributes.name: Arcade Worker?

attributes.content: (How good could the girl be? This'll definitely buy enough time.)
attributes.name: Arcade Worker?

attributes.content: Hmmm... Cardi will probably like that snowboard, huh?
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Now that I think about it, I really wanna see Cardi on the snow!
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Okay, let's give it a try, I'll get it in one go. Bring it on!
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Let's take your entry fee first, and we'll keep your bag for you in the cabinet back there.
attributes.name: Arcade Worker?

attributes.content: It's true about Lungmen! We've been walking for ages and only covered two blocks. My feet are dying!
attributes.name: Cardigan

attributes.content: That's because you keep pulling us into every store, and spend hours picking and choosing without ever actually buying anything.
attributes.name: Adnachiel

attributes.content: That's because my wallet is already basically empty!
attributes.name: Cardigan

attributes.content: Yeah, I remember seeing that baseball glove and bat you ordered a couple of days ago.
attributes.name: Adnachiel

attributes.content: Those are apology gifts for Cuora! And I had to sell some old stuff to make up what I was short...
attributes.name: Cardigan

attributes.content: Oh? Have you and Cuora not yet reconciled?
attributes.name: May

attributes.content: I remember you two quarreling something fierce in the game room... First time I've ever seen Cuora bite a person.
attributes.name: May

attributes.content: Thinking back on it... it was my fault.
attributes.name: Cardigan

attributes.content: I can just be too carefree sometimes, assuming everyone's always out to have fun with each other, no joke that can't be made...
attributes.name: Cardigan

attributes.content: The medic operators say Cuora's obsession with protecting her backpack is subconscious. Since she's forgotten most of her past, no one knows exactly where it comes from...
attributes.name: Adnachiel

attributes.content: She's even forgotten her family and friends... Pretty sad, when you think about it.
attributes.name: May

attributes.content: But she told me that after making friends at Rhodes Island, she doesn't feel so lonely anymore.
attributes.name: May

attributes.content: By the way, I haven't seen her since early this morning. Where's she gone off to?
attributes.name: May

attributes.content: Sigh... she's probably still avoiding me...
attributes.name: Cardigan

attributes.content: Ha-yah!
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Wh... what? You hit the red zone again? How are you that lucky?
attributes.name: Arcade Worker?

attributes.content: Hah!
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: You hit it again?!
attributes.name: Arcade Worker?

attributes.content: No... is the difficulty set too low? I think I can adjust the ball direction and blocks here...
attributes.name: Arcade Worker?

attributes.content: Again!
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Wow! So you can throw out balls that change direction, and put up some more blocks... Hah, alright, I'll get serious too.
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Phew! I feel fantastic. This is the joy of baseball!
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Got some more balls? Send them my way!
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Is... is this really happening?
attributes.name: Arcade Worker?

attributes.content: I maxed out the difficulty!
attributes.name: Arcade Worker?

attributes.content: Her stance, her strength, her precision...
attributes.name: Arcade Worker?

attributes.content: Is this girl Ambrois Edwards?!
attributes.name: Arcade Worker?

attributes.content: Hey, how many points did I get? Did I win the prize?
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Um... the scoring system is overloaded or something, but just looking at it, you definitely cleared 475...
attributes.name: Arcade Worker?

attributes.content: (Shit! Daai goh just left, he can't have found the pendant yet... What do I do? I have to buy him some more time.)
attributes.name: Arcade Worker?

attributes.content: Then let me get that snowboard!
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Err, okay... No, wait! I think you're not quite satisfied yet, miss. Would you like to hit a few more balls?
attributes.name: Arcade Worker?

attributes.content: But I already won the prize... I guess I do want to play some more. Do I have to pay?
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: No, you got the prize, and since nobody else is around, you can keep playing until we close!
attributes.name: Arcade Worker?

attributes.content: The ball flies toward Cuora, and in the split second before it passes through the corner of her vision, she swings her bat forcefully—
To the sight of the 'arcade worker' the girl's figure seems to overlap with all the baseball stars he's ever seen.
The ball once again nails the center zone. At which point the pitching machine malfunctions, emitting sparks and giving off an uncomfortable sound.
What... what's happening?
attributes.name: Arcade Worker?

attributes.content: BOOM—
Good heavens! I heard that explosion just now, I'm sure we're getting caught up in another incident here now...
attributes.name: May

attributes.content: Sounds like it came from that mall over there. Say, what's that on the ground...?
attributes.name: Adnachiel

attributes.content: That's Cuora's backpack!
attributes.name: Cardigan

attributes.content: Oh no... is Cuora in danger?!
attributes.name: Cardigan

attributes.content: Over here! Cuora's here!
attributes.name: May

attributes.content: Cuora! Cuora!
attributes.name: Cardigan

attributes.content: She's fine, just looks like she's sleeping. Oh? What's that she's holding...?
attributes.name: Adnachiel

attributes.content: It's a... snowboard?
attributes.name: Cardigan

attributes.content: Ugh...
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Where... am I? Rhodes Island?
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: I remember... I was playing baseball, and then there was a boom...
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: What happened next...? Where'd those two guys go?
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: I was having so much fun, I didn't get a chance to thank them...
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: But hey, I think Lungmenites are really friendly!
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Oh! Yeah! My prize! Where's the snowboard I got for Cardi?!
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Phew, it's not broken.
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: And my gifts for the others, they're all still here.
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Come in!
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Oh, Cardi...
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Um...
attributes.name: Cardigan and Cuora

attributes.content: You first, Cuora.
attributes.name: Cardigan

attributes.content: Um, okay! This snowboard I won at the mall.. it's for you! I'm sorry about that thing before!
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: So the snowboard was for me...?
attributes.name: Cardigan

attributes.content: I heard some of the others say you wanted to be a skier...
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: And I remembered you had some ski clothes, so I thought...
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Oh, those clothes...
attributes.name: Cardigan

attributes.content: Heh, well, I kinda ran into a little financial trouble last month and, well... I sold them...
attributes.name: Cardigan

attributes.content: Well, I can get you some new ski clothes next time. Or is there something else you want?
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Hmmm... let me think.
attributes.name: Cardigan

attributes.content: Sure! Just say the word!
attributes.name: Cuora

attributes.content: Cardigan offers a new baseball bat to Cuora, then raises her other hand, waving it in front of the girl.
It is covered by a baseball glove.
Alright... I want you to teach me to play baseball! Starting today!
attributes.name: Cardigan
